{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858038855,"sessionID":"ses_2869d2f0dffezZ3nBI50Cg90xh","part":{"id":"prt_d796337fd001KG2vmFWyCxS364","messageID":"msg_d7963042c001vxRD1SVlDObGV4","sessionID":"ses_2869d2f0dffezZ3nBI50Cg90xh","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_tool-c4ddfcbe659547539befd5981100e09a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"PicoD|AR-015"},"output":"Found 71 matches\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\n  Line 3: AR: AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-015 Delta Specification: PicoD 命令执行 API\n  Line 5: 实现 PicoD HTTP 守护进程的命令执行 API，为 AgentCube 平台的代码解释器沙箱提供安全的代码执行和文件管理能力。PicoD 在可配置的工作区 jail 中运行命令，管理工作区文件，并暴露健康检查端点和 JWT（RSA）保护的 API。\n  Line 9: - code-execution/spec.md: PicoD 命令执行 API 规范，包含所有 API 端点和行为的详细定义\n  Line 10: - code-execution/design.md: PicoD 设计文档，从源码推导的数据结构、常量和实现细节\n  Line 12: - proposal.md: AR-015 提案文档，概述 PicoD 的目的、范围、设计和实现策略\n  Line 22: - **WHEN** PicoD 服务器启动\n  Line 30: - **WHEN** PicoD 服务器启动\n  Line 36: - **WHEN** PicoD 服务器启动\n  Line 41: - **GIVEN** PicoD 服务器启动\n  Line 307: - **AND** JSON 包含 `service` 为 `\"PicoD\"`\n  Line 409: - **GIVEN** 使用 `-port 9090` 启动 PicoD\n  Line 414: - **GIVEN** 使用 `-workspace /data/workspace` 启动 PicoD\n  Line 419: - **GIVEN** 使用任何 klog 标志启动 PicoD\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API\n  Line 5: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that provides secure command execution and file management capabilities within a configurable workspace jail. It exposes JWT-protected APIs for code execution, file operations (upload, list, download), and an unauthenticated health check endpoint. PicoD serves as the core execution engine for code interpreter sandboxes in the AgentCube platform.\n  Line 9: Define and implement the command execution API for the PicoD daemon, enabling secure code execution and management of interpreter sessions in an isolated workspace environment.\n  Line 105:    - Requires PicoD container in sandbox pods\n  Line 107:    - Routes invocation requests to PicoD endpoint\n  Line 110:    - Forwards execution requests to PicoD instances\n  Line 112:    - Handles PicoD health check responses\n  Line 115:    - Includes PicoD in container image\n  Line 117:    - Manages PicoD lifecycle (start, stop, health checks)\n  Line 120:    - Adds PicoD container to code interpreter pod template\n  Line 122:    - Exposes PicoD port in pod spec\n  Line 125:    - Builds PicoD Docker image (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`)\n  Line 126:    - Runs unit and integration tests for PicoD\n  Line 127:    - Deploys PicoD images to container registry\n  Line 130:    - Includes PicoD client for code execution\n  Line 145: │   Router    │ ───────────────────►  │   PicoD     │ ─────────────────► │  Command    │\n  Line 237: - Cannot create executable files via PicoD API\n  Line 244: **Description**: Allow PicoD to operate without JWT authentication if public key is missing\n  Line 444:   \"service\": \"PicoD\",\n  Line 610:    - PicoD runs inside cluster (uses mTLS via service mesh)\n  Line 680: | `-port` | int | `8080` | Port for the PicoD server to listen on |\n  Line 692: # Start PicoD with default settings\n  Line 695: # Start PicoD with custom port and workspace\n  Line 718: 1. Integrate PicoD into sandbox pod template\n  Line 720: 3. Update Router to forward to PicoD\n  Line 839: - How to use PicoD APIs\n  Line 855: - ConfigMap: (optional) PicoD configuration\n  Line 859: - PicoD base image (to be built)\n  Line 983: │  PicoD Health Check │\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/CHANGE.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n  Line 4: - **AR**: AR-015\n  Line 5: - **Title**: PicoD 命令执行 API\n  Line 12: Define the command execution API for the PicoD daemon, enabling secure code execution and management of interpreter sessions.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-015 Implementation Summary\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/README.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-015 Implementation Notes\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/spec.md:\n  Line 1: # PicoD 命令执行 API Specification\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-015/design.md:\n  Line 1: # PicoD 命令执行 API Design\n  Line 3: ## AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md:\n  Line 105:     publicKey         []byte               // PicoD 公钥（authMode=picod 时注入）\n  Line 476: | `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModePicoD` | AuthMode=picod 时注入公钥 |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-003/design.md:\n  Line 950: - Enforced by the PicoD daemon\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/design.md:\n  Line 72: │  │  PicoD Daemon   │  │  Session Store  │  │  Router     │ │\n  Line 1044: ### With PicoD Daemon\n  Line 1242: - Enforced by the PicoD daemon\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md:\n  Line 26: ## 4. PicoD (Go) - 执行引擎隔离测试\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test_spec.md:\n  Line 19: ## 4. 编码执行引擎测试 (PicoD)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7